AGI -&nbsp; "Marco Mottola telephoned me, told me 'they heard me in Frosinone and asked me where I was on June 1, 2001 and if I went to the Chioppetelle bar'. Then he added 'I said I didn't remember and that certainly if I was in that bar the only person I could be with was you'. And finally concluded with 'safely they will also call tea. I've never been to that bar." Laura Ricci, engaged to Marco Mottola in 2002 in front of the Court of Appeal of Rome during the trial on the murder of Serena Mollicone>, the young girl of Arce killed in 2001.
&nbsp;
"I couldn't confirm it because I wasn't there," he added. "At the time I was 17 years old, I had a certain idea but later I reassessed my opinions, thought I was used," as alibi and said. "Di Marco I thought he was a normal guy > and not strong from the physical point of view - he says -. It wasn't a strong character, it didn't take positions, no matter what I said. And on the hair he said that "sometimes he brought the chips, then he cut them. In the period when we were together he had them brushed."
&nbsp;
"With me it was always nice when we were together, but then after we broke up it didn't calculate me exactly - he said -. When he started shooting the voice he thought it was he who killed Serena was sick: especially when he knew he was supposed to move. When we passed in front of William's cartolery he always said, Serena's dad is 'convinced that I did it.' As to the hypothesis that he could be the author of Serena's murder, Ricci added: "I always thought if he could do something like this, he would have helped others," he explained.

